reviews: A wonderful boutique hotel, beautiful good size rooms, excellent bathrooms and toiletries, a lovely pool and hamam room to relax. Great location just around the corner from commerce metro station and the staff were attentive and kind. We will definitely use this hotel again when we are back in Paris.

Absolutely beautiful hotel, great friendly service in the heart of Paris. We had booked this hotel after our flight was cancelled. On arrival we were given the warmest welcome and went straight up to the rooftop terrace. We were also upgraded to s junior suite which was greatly appreciated after the disappointment of a cancelled flight. It was a sunny day and we enjoyed a peaceful drink on the terrace where a very attentive young man came to take our orders. We then went for dinner in the restaurant up the road and came back to use the spa which had a lovely big pool , steam room and showers. The hotel is exceptional, excellent level of cleanliness , every employee greets you when you pass by. 15 min walk to Eiffel Tower and lots of bars and restaurants and french bakeries in the area.

I have been to Paris ten times over my lifetime and this is by far the best hotel I have stayed in. I have been to more upscale places but this was definitely the best value. It was worth every penny.
We stayed in in room 602 and we had a nice size suite with a large bathroom by Paris standards. The room was spotless and we had a lot of storage space. The only downside was the roof too sky lights which be a wearing an eye patch to bed.
We had the floor to Ourselves since there were o my 2 rooms on this floor. This was a concern to us in the Covid era.
The hotel is small and only had 39 rooms,
There is a nice lap pool in the basement which I swam in daily. It was well heated.
There is a small gym which is adequate as well as a steam room.
The staff and service in the hotel are 5 star. They could not be more helpful. We received several gifts during our stay which we appreciated.
Our room had 2 terraces one of which had a view of the Eiffel Tower.
Though the hotel is not in a touristy area you are only a 5 minute walk to line 8 of the metro which connects to most major sights.
Rue de Commerce is around the corner which is a lively shopping street .
The hotel itself is on a quiet street good for sleeping .
If we return again we will stay here.

We chose this hotel because it was close to the friend I was visiting. We arrived before noon and hoped to just leave our luggage and begin our day touring Paris, but our room was already ready and we were able to get settled first, which was such a nice surprise. The staff was super friendly and the room was clean and comfortable. I appreciated the in-room coffee maker.

Be careful if reserving they take a nights pay as a deposit then when you cancel take ages to refund and then hold your money for almost 2 weeks without telling you before it comes back into your account.

Communication is really poor when they have taken your money also.

Being a first time visitor to Paris & looking at many different hotel options (which was a bit overwhelming) we settled on this little gem and it did not disappoint. The rooms are as expected for a European hotel - compact. However the bathroom was a good size and the shower was wonderful! The bed was very comfy as well. It has a very nice pool & sauna which we used after doing a lot of walking. There is the option of adding breakfast at this hotel for an extra charge (similar cost to what we paid at local bistros for breakfast), however we did not do this. We used Uber when our feet were tired of walking but there was metro stations close by as well as a bus stop just down the block. Adam the concierge was so helpful and friendly. Was definitely a great place for our trip!

Great mid-price hotel. Well considered design with some stylish touches. Much better than staying in a generic brand hotel. Quality breakfast offering and a great coffee machine in my room too!
Staff were friendly and always ready to help. After a long day of work it was a real treat to be able to make use of the pool and gym. Very restorative. On this occasion I was in Paris on business but I would happily stay here with the family for leisure.

We liked the location of the hotel it was near the tube trains and within a 20 minute walk from the Eifeel tower. There were shops, bars and restaurants nearby.

The communication from the hotel regarding directions to get there was really helpful.

The reception staff were especially friendly and accomodating with requests. We stayed in room 501 in the front of the hotel, there was some noise in the street in the mornings but this would not put me off staying again.

I used the swimming pool which was really nice. The only recommendation I would have is to ensure that the staff show guests where the swimming pool is and how to access everything. I was alone down there which felt a bit isolating especially as the door to go into the pool is not the door to come out of the pool, which I was unaware of.

I would have no hesitation in recommending this hotel.

Lovely hotel, helpful and friendly staff. Lovely spa area, terrace and room. I would recommend and I would stay again next time I’m in Paris. Central but quiet area. All the amenities I would need in the room.

The hotel is located nicely, not too far from the Eiffel Tower however on our arrival we we "pleasantly" greeted by a massive still fence covering the front view of the hotel with rubbish bins strewn everywhere on the pavement.

Enter the hotels and we were greeted by a lovely man called Adam. Him and the other staff are the reason the hotel gets some stars as the staff were amazing. We were given a 5th floor room which was apparently one of their better rooms with the "best" view however we had full view of the buildings across the road. The carpet had cigarette burns in it but aside from that the staff clearly put some effort in to make it feel welcoming.

Generally I mention that pictures dont do something justice however the picture genuinely have been taken cleverly to make the hotel look much better than it really is.

I read reviews about how amazing the breakfast is. There is a photo someone posted of a table with breakfast supplies include cut meats, that pretty much is the main serving of breakfast.

Luckily we were only there 2 nights as we arrived at 12 midnight the first night and were out most of the following day thus pointless complaining or requesting a room change. Aside from that the hotel is clean, our shower could do with some mechanical TLC however still clean.

Once again, the staff at this hotel are amazing though. I do feel there are much better accommodations closer to better amenities for similar price. So be wise in your choice.

A little heart of tranquillity and relaxation with great access to central Paris. Great for variety of local patisseries and restaurants. The room was comfortable and clean with great shower.
The food and service was good and we'd definitely return!

We just had the best few days in this hotel and literally cannot fault it. The location is brilliant - such a nice quiet area but with plenty of bars and places to eat. We spent a lot of time at the A La Tour Eiffel bar round the corner, just happily people watching. The hotel staff are friendly and attentive, the whole place is spotless and what made the entire trip was our room! We stayed in the Eiffel Tower terrace suite and it was simply amazing. We also had the romantic package as it was my boyfriend’s birthday and was so worth it. The view from the terrace is something we will never forget. Touches like having breakfast in your room and getting sole use of the pool on night 1 really made the trip special. We had the best time and will 100% be back in the future. Thank you so much!

We just returned from a 5 day stay at this hotel, it was wonderful.
The hotel is a little gem, the staff were friendly efficient and nothing was too much trouble. The facilities a spa pool and location were great We had the roof top suite which had views of the Paris skyline and the Eiffel Tower. There are cafes and restaurants close by. We will definitely return.

This is a really nice place to stay in Paris. It's not a large hotel (all the better for it) but it is thoughtfully designed to make maximum use of the available space. As advertised, there is a peaceful rooftop garden, plants hanging from balconies, as well as a small swimming pool and hammam. In other words, it's a great place to relax before and after spending the day in the city. Again, the rooms are not large, but they are absolutely functional, the beds are really comfortable, and with good bathroom facilities. The location is also great with the Rue du Commerce just around the corner, and plenty of interesting streets and neighbourhoods to explore within a short cycling distance. And finally, the people who work at the hotel are all very professional and friendly, which makes it a particular pleasure to stay there. Very much recommended.

We stayed 5 days in the hotel. It is a small, intimate, nice hotel. The rooms are quite small but functionally very well operating with a modern shower mechanism.
The buffet breakfast is good, but limited in varietes compared with larger international hotels.
Hotel has an indoor swimming pool, and a steam room. The water was warm and I had a few nice swims there.

The service was very good without an exception.The personnel are very helpful and kind.
I especially like to mention two professional young ladys that served us extremely well.

After a busy, crowded, chaotic day of sightseeing,
this Hotel was our refuge. EVERYTHING about this hotel and its staff is fantastic. The breakfast staff met us each morning with a friendly smile. One of us has a dairy allergy and the they made sure that we had tasty non-dairy alternatives each day. The reception desk staff were friendly and helpful when we wanted to add an extra day to our visit. The suite was very clean and comfortable, and much larger than typical Paris hotel rooms. The hotel gardens are quiet, beautiful spaces to relax. I can't say enough good things about this place. Don't pass it up, it is a must stay.

What a perfect stay we had, the reception, the service, the room, the pool…everything was perfect 🤩 we almost did not want to leave the hotel to explore Paris 🤣we will be back for sure. Good location, with good access to public transport.

I booked this hotel on the basis of the Tripadvisor reviews and they were not wrong!Fabulous hotel all round, small and modern, comfy beds, lovely linen, quiet and peaceful at night we slept really well. The pool is lovely and even better than the photographs, warm and spotlessly clean. Lovely fourth floor terrace with a glimpse of the Eiffel Tower. Great area for shops, restaurants, cafes and several metro stations. Staff were very helpful pre our arrival and answered emails promptly - all in all a fabulous stay. There is a tea shop called le jardins des mademoiselles so make sure you have the night venue!

Amazing hotel in a great location. The staff were very pleasant and helpful throughout the trip. My wife really enjoyed her birthday surprise organised by the hotel on the second day of our trip, and the restaurant recommendations were brilliant (restaurant called ‘Abstinence’ has to be the best restaurant I have ever been to). Will definitely stay here when i visit again.

This hotel is conveniently located in a nice neighborhood with many cafés, restaurants and shops nearby (incl an organic carrefour and an excellent vegetarian restaurant). The staff is exceptional, both during and prior to our visit. They were so helpful getting us tickets, finding us restaurants etc. and we were even able to get into our rooms before check in. The spa is great, after a long day in Paris just relaxing in the pool and steam bath. Comfortable beds and pillows, lovely bathroom. We requested a quiet room and got one, facing the garden. We didn't use the restaurant but found a bag of fresh madeleines and a recyclable bottle of water to welcome us. All in all the hotel added to the great experience we had in Paris.

Everything about this hotel is great, the service, the swimming pool, the sauna, the breakfast. A nice walk away from the Eiffel Tower. There are restaurants, shops and bars nearby the hotel. Parking at 5 minutes distance.

Good location (near the Commerce Metro stop & the 70 Bus) A very helpful staff (spoke many languages besides French & English). It is a nice new small boutique like hotel with AC which is important in late July & August. They have a lovely small garden sitting area on the 4th Floor for an early before dinner or after dinner drink. We plan to stay here again when we return.

We stay in August with our family. The pool and roof top deck was wonderful to relax at the end of a long day. The neighborhood had many great restaurants. When we go back to Paris we will definitely stay here again.

I cannot praise enough this beautiful hotel for the way they looked after us, in particular Alexandra who made us feel like home and welcomed us lik friends, not as customers. From the very beginning when I’ve made the booking, until check out, she’s been up and beyond to make sure we will truly enjoy celebrate our wonderful anniversary in this cosy hotel.
Thank you Valerie for keeping on board amazing staff members like Alexandra, we hope to see you again in the near future xx
We highly recommend this hotel

6 hours into our stay here at Les Jardines de Mademoiselle and already in love with the location, the hotel and the staff. Anaëlle was providing wonderful helpful information even prior to our arrival and it really started our trip out on the right foot. The rooms are very pretty, clean and have all of the amenities that we need, including delicious macaroons :-D The location is walking distance to fantastic bars and restaurants and we can wait to keep exploring the city as our trip continues.

A new building in a particularly appealing part of Paris. Close to the Metropolitain; lots of very good restaurants close by; rue du Commerce with plenty of shops is just around the corner. No parking at the hotel and no 5 minute parking in front either and we noted that cars parked in the street on a Monday were all papered with E35 parking tickets. There is a parking building about 7 minutes walk away.
(Prepay for parking through Parclick or similar and get a lower rate than advised to me by the hotel. You also get unlimited entries and exits for the duration of your booking). Staff were all excellent, spoke English fluently and couldn't have been more helpful. Housekeeping is of a very high standard.

There is a swimming pool and a hammam at the first level souterrain which is a nice bonus.

The very small lobby and bar has seating for less than 10 people. Perhaps because of that, we didn't see anyone using the bar during our 4 nights.

Everything about this hotel was small, except for the bathroom. We booked a "comfort" room at E190 per night but comfortable it was not. Using the term "comfort" to describe the room is seriously misleading. We carried two overhead-locker-size suitcases but there was no space to leave them out, even zipped up. The edge of the bed had gone soft on one side, perhaps from people using it as a seat. There was one small chair in the corner of the room that blocked off easy access to the very small wardrobe. Getting to the bathroom in the middle of the night was a matter of bouncing off obstructions en route.

The breakfast area is equally small and is therefore cramped. The offering at E17 includes cereals and hot dishes. We checked it out - the hot dishes may or may not appeal (they didn't to us) so we opted to eat at one of the nearby brasseries for somewhat less cost.

We have been staying at some of the brand-name hotels during our tour of la belle France and should have stuck with them. Rooms are larger and more comfortable, generally, and not priced as high as this hotel. We think this hotel is overpriced. Despite trying hard it is hampered by being cramped and small.

We stayed here for 3 nights in october 2019. The location of the hotel is excellent, close to the commerce metro station, within 30-45 minutes walk of main Paris attractions and a great selection of bars and restaurants close by. The spa, gym and pool facilities are great. Would definitely recommend this hotel

Stayed here for my birthday and the hotel was very modern and nice. Superior room was a bit too small though. Was about €6 to get to the Eiffel Tower by Uber which was ok. The rooftop area was nice, the pool and steam room was great. We asked for late check out unaware there was a massive cost due to miscommunication between my bf and the receptionist, then we were charged €60 at check out. I’ve stayed in other places and they never charged us. The receptionist wasn’t very nice about it. Bit unfortunate but apart from that really enjoyed my stay here.

It's not 10/10 perfect as a hotel but there's a lot to like about Les Jardins de Mademoiselle: the rooms are very nice, the bed comfy, the bathrooms well-appointed with a superb shower; a tranquil roof garden full of fragrant rosemary bushes, raspberry plants and olive trees; friendly and obliging staff; a brilliant location - bang in the centre of town but tucked away down a quiet avenue.

The only blip for us was that we had to call reception to turn on the air-conditioning in our room as there was no controller in the room but we'll give them the benefit of the doubt as we were only there for one night and perhaps other rooms have controllers in them.

We really liked this hotel.
We stayed in the Eiffel Tower suite.
Lovely pool, great bed, good shower and just a really nice, relaxed feel.

The restaurants and shops of the Commerce district and its Metro station are a short 5 minute walk away.
We walked to the Eiffel tower from here.

Book it, before everyone else finds it.

A nice contemporary hotel few blocks from the Commerce metro station (line 8), with very attentive front desk, reliable service and a very modern, clean interior. Rooms are small but very practical, clean with very comfortable beds, modern bath, and a safe. There is a place in the inner court to sit down and relax. For more active visitors, there is a very nice size indoor swimming pool in the basement (I would guess about 15m length) and a steam room. Both open daily till 22:30. Bath robes and slippers provided. We have not tried the breakfast. This hotel will be definitely on my list when visiting Paris again.

We had a wonderful stay at "Les Jardins de Mademoiselle"! The receptionists were very friendly, the room was very clean and modern. There's also a beautiful spa and a nice small garden and terrasse, which gives the place a very cosy feel to it. Plus, we felt very safe in this neighbourhood.

Stayed one night with family at the last minute. Staff were kind and informative. Loved the pool, steam room and rooftop garden. The dinner recommendation was spot on. The room was recently renovated, beds were comfortable and showers spotless. We would give 10 stars if we could.

The hotel is very welcoming with an excellent spa and terrace overlooking a typical Paris internal courtyard. The breakfast is adequate but there is very very little space between the tables. The large double room was adequately furnished and had a very small balcony overlooking the Rue de Mademoiselle.

We stayed in the "family room," which was 2 adjoining rooms. Our room was clean, comfortable, modern and had all the necessities we needed. The rooms were amazingly quiet - even with the adjoining rooms, we never heard anyone in the other room, no TV sounds, etc. Each day we were left with 2 bottles of water, turn down service at night, and excellent cleaning service. The room has a good hair dryer and shampoo, soap, etc. The hotel and rooms also have A/C, which was definitely needed in July.

The staff at Les Jardins de Madamoiselle were ALL over the top in their customer service. They were helpful as we planned our days, attentive to every need, very friendly, polite, and accommodating. We arrived very early and they worked to get us in our room that morning, offering us cold water and croissants and suggestions for things to do as we waited. Sophie and Alexandra were especially helpful and their English is perfect!

The hotel has a pool, which our kids enjoyed especially during the heat wave. It's clean and nice. There is also a nice steam room. We also spent time on the outside terrace which had comfortable sitting areas and lots of wonderful smells from all of the herbs growing there. It is beautiful! You can order service from the terrace and they will bring you whatever you need.

The hotel is very conveniently located - less than 30 minutes walk to the Eiffel Tower, less than a minute to the bus station, and 5 minutes to the metro station. There are tons of really good restaurants and shops and several grocery stores close by. It really is in a wonderful, safe location that is out of the crowds and noise but close to everywhere you want to go.

There is nothing I would change about this hotel or its staff. We had a perfect stay (6 nights) and would definitely stay there again. We hated to leave! I highly recommend Les Jardins de Mademoiselle!

Spent 2 nights and 3 days here, 2 adults and 2 children, and really loved it. Reception staff are very friendly and helpful. Boys really enjoyed the pool and we enjoyed the spa. Happy hour was more like happy 4 hours and the garden and roof terrace are a great place to relax at the end of a busy day. We had an interconnecting room which was very modern and well equipped. Hotel is a 5 minute Uber ride from the Eiffel Tower and big shopping mall a 10 minute walk. Plenty of restaurants and cafes within minutes. Will definitely go back.

A very nice hotel, great stuff, clean quiet place, amazing service. The pool was excellent, clean, warm. Breakfast - fantastic. Everything was to perfection. The area around the hotel full of cosy cafes and restaurants.

My mother and I visited Paris in July 2019 to see the sights, as one does. We stayed in Les Jardins de Madamoiselle for 3 nights, and were happily suprised by the quality of the accommodation and facilities. The swimming pool was just long enough for lengths, and the steam room was warm and comfortable. The gym left a little to be desired, but considering it was in the basement of a relatively small hotel it was still a nice facility to have.
The rooms themselves were modern, clean and comfortable, if a little small; the air con was efficient and quiet; the shower was powerful; and most rooms command a lovely view over either the street or interior garden. My mum was especially pleased to be able to see the Eiffel Tower from her suite on the top floor.
The hotel is situated near many lovely restaurants and cafés (more than enough for a different restaurant each day of a visit) and we found that the eiffel tower could be reached in half an hour of walking. The hotel is also very near the Commerce metro station on line 8.
All in all this hotel was fantastic. I would thoroughly recommend it to anyone travelling to Paris on holiday.

Terrific cosy hotel in a nice neighborhood in Paris, convenient to everything but away from most of the bustle and noise. Well designed and comfortable rooms, lots of outdoor patio / garden space, a nice breakfast, and terrific lap pool / steam room and small gym. Staff were very friendly and professional. Metro is less than a three minute walk and there is a great choice of practical shops, restaurants and bars nearby.

I happened to find Les Jardins de Mademoiselle doing a search on Expedia. I am so glad I booked this amazing hotel. We stayed here for a weekend but I was so impressed by the staff, location and the facilities. The hotel is within a 10 minute walk to Cambronne station and right around the corner from a bus stop. You are near several brasseries, patisseries, grocery stores, etc. This is a very quiet area at night so if you like being off the beaten path then this is the place. The staff were amazingly helpful in every way. The breakfast has some very delicious choices or you are close to other breakfast options. The pool area reminds me of a hotel in Zermatt Switzerland where I have stayed. Our Uber drivers didn’t even realize it was a hotel because it has the look of a residential building versus a hotel. We were informed my one very talkative Uber driver that we were within 15 min of Roland Garros. This is a great find and I highly recommend it. When I get back to Paris, I will definitely want to stay again!

My wife and I had an excellent stay at the Hotel.
This is one of the best hotel we stayed. We travel around the world often, and find the staff is friendly and want to make sure our stay is comfortable. In particular Sofia, she paid attention to all the details to make sure we are well taken care of during our visit.
The location is excellent, close to Metro, nice restaurant, and Eiffel Tower and also other attractions.
They have a pool and spa, that is world class, make you relax after a days work.
I would give a five star rating

I stayed at Les Jardins de Mademoiselle for my girlfriends 21st birthday. The Superior room with a terrace balcony was amazing. The hotel arranged balloons, flowers, a personalised cake, rose petals etc as requested, it was all arranged fantastically. 5 stars overall; Clean and good location, spa facilities are also very nice. I wouldn’t change anything about the stay and I would highly recommend this hotel.

We were delighted by this hotel in the 15th arrondissement of Paris! It's very close to the Commerce metro station, but still located in a quieter, residential part of the city, so there were very few tourists and no crowds. Adorable shops around the corner with plenty of great local bistros and cafes for dinner/drinks in the evenings, if you don't want to stray far from the hotel. The hotel itself is beautiful, comfortable, nicely appointed, and clean. Delicious, robust breakfast offered in the mornings. Both the courtyard gardens and the rooftop terrace offer FABULOUS locations for a breakfast coffee or an evening glass of Bordeaux (which they sell at the bar) in a quiet, classically Parisian setting. Their kind, helpful, English-speaking staff that really made our stay wonderful. We will definitely be staying here on our next trip to Paris!

Had a wonderful stay at this hotel! The front desk staff were super helpful from giving restaurant recommendations to providing me an adapter while I was there. Not one staff member was rude or unpleasant. The grounds were well maintained, rooms were beautiful and the bathrobes made it feel like a 5 star experience. Only a mile away from the Eiffel Tower and super close to metro stations. Highly recommend staying here!

Very nice staff, clean room, diverse breakfast. I had a room with view to the interior garden and it was perfect: I didn’t hear a single car passing by and I slept very well, which almost never happens when I travel.

This hotel was very nice and close to the city. Plenty of Shopping and restaurants. Train is about 1-2 blocks away. Also you can walk to Eiffel Tower. Love the indoor pool and the hospitality of the staff. Will stay again, perfect hotel!

Stayed here for a long weekend with family and loved it. Great location - Eurospar next door, loads of cafes and bars, Metro station 200 yards, fresh fruit shop and chocolatiers 100 yards. 20min brisk walk to Eiffel Tower but you’re bound to stop for a coffee en route! Beautiful underground pool (good for kids and couples) with nice gym and sauna etc. Brilliant staff - they put on an all day Easter Egg hunt whilst we were there and really made extra effort. Rooftop terrace is great feature, you feel amongst the skyline and can see the tip of the Eiffel Tower - nice touch at night. Hotel is new so great time to book, it felt fairly quiet which was good - think there are only 40 rooms. No need to pre-book breakfast, pay as you go - plenty places nearby anyway. Hopefully will come back to Paris and will definitely book this hotel.

Great hotel, great neighborhood! Very friendly, nice rooms, great outdoor garden, and the location can't be beat. This hotel is better for a second trip as it is not near the "classic" tourist attractions. But if you are going to Paris and want to live like a native, this is your place.

Les Jardins de Mademoiselle is one year old, located in a quaint residential Parisienne neighborhood convenient to all of Paris via the Metro. The lobby is small but modern and clean. There is a small outside private garden to sit. The breakfast room is a tiny "L" shape with barely enough room for the servers to work. The receptionist, Anna (I believe) was welcoming and allowed us our room early. Our room was small but modern and had a balcony. Breakfast was very good and well beyond continental. My only complaint occurred just before checkout. Our flight was delayed so I wanted to change the time of my taxi pick-up from 7 am to later. I tried calling the front desk for nearly 40 minutes with no one answering. What would have happened if me or a guest suffered an emergency such as medical or if we were attacked? I spoke to the receptionist who said that he had to go downstairs and set-up breakfast. I told him that he should have a cell phone which he said he did but it did not work. He told management. This is a horrible breach of faith for a hotel that we paid nearly $220 per night. Would I stay here again? Probably not. Would I recommend it to others? Probably not.

We were welcomed by Alexandra at the reception who is very friendly and super helpful with all information and requests.

The bed and pillows are very comfy. What I like the most is the bathroom, which is spacious with good water pressure. It has lots of shelves to put our toiletries too and the heated rack is also a plus.

This hotel also has a nice heated swimming pool with a ‘hammam’ (sauna) which became handy when Paris had the yellow vests strike. It’s also very nice to have the bathrobes and slippers provided in the room to complement the visit to the pool.

This was my second time staying at this boutique hotel. A very friendly, professional hotel, rooms are modern & clean. Good central location, perfect Parisien bistro suburb. Reception staff are very attentive & cant do enough for you. That’s why I came back & will go again.

Very nice 4* boutique hotel in Paris.

Pro: Friendly and helpful staffs, nice modern and clean rooms, tea/coffee facilities, comfy beds, spa, pool and hammam facilities, great breakfast

Con: A bit out of the way from main sites using the nearest metro but near bus stop that bring you to St Germain and Pont d’Alma

Spent a perfect few days away with my boyfriend at this lovely hotel. We were welcomed to our room with a lovely surprise of macaroons as it was my boyfriends birthday. The room was small but perfect for what we needed. The staff were all lovely and welcoming and keen to help us with anything. The hotel was in a great area, about 20 minute walk to the Eiffel Tower and very close to a metro stations along with all the shops you could need. Hotel was clearly very new and tidy and very well decorated. Perfect hotel for a perfect few days away. Thank you very much.

Everything was amazing and my 6th stay in Parus. Immaculate, friendly staff, comfy beds, annex overlooking gardens do peaceful and shops on doorstep - definitely coming back - spa lovely just pool needs heating but was empty so still enjoyed very much

We enjoy yes our time at les Jardins de Mademoiselle. Nice boutique hotel, exceptional service, all new and modern. Well kept, very clean. A lot of shopping and restaurants very near by. Will recommend to family and friends.

Having stayed at lots of hotels in Paris I found a gem of a hotel near the Eiffel Tower. It’s a small boutique hotel but with lovely suites and rooms. We booked the Eiffel Tower suite and it was definitely worth it. So lovely to have a private rooftop terrace and to see the Eiffel Tower.
They have another communal terrace which is also very pretty. In the lower ground floor they have a wonderful pool and spa. The staff are so charming and happy to help with everything. It’s now my new “go to “ hotel in Paris and I wouldn’t want to stay anywhere else. Amazing stay.

We stayed 3 nights in this very nice little hotel in the middle of a very nice district of Paris, away from the tourists frenzy. The hotel is clean, the rooms are new and charming, the little garden in the middle gives you a feeling of rest. It is also very quiet and the staff are very friendly. We would stay there again without any doubt.

Had a wonderful stay at the hotel last week whilst exploring Paris. Hotel is very conveniently located in a delightful, safe, and accessible neighbourhood. Very short walk to Commerce Metro, making it simple to reach any part of the city (handy if you are arriving by Eurostar). Having said this, we felt it was a pleasant walk to (or at least back from) any of the major sights along the Seine, so opted to do this most days. It is also a direct walk to the Eiffel Tower. We were always greeted by friendly and welcoming staff, who were keen to help and ensure our stay was comfortable. The room was small by American standards, but reasonable for a European city hotel. Our room (which overlooked the quiet courtyard) was always cleaned thoroughly and had everything we needed for a short stay. The pool was immaculate. We did not have breakfast as there are many delicious boulangeries/shops in the area.
Overall, this is a great hotel if you want a clean and comfortable base for exploring Paris, which is located a convenient distance from the 'tourist-trap' areas. I hope this new hotel maintains these high standards, so we can use it as our 'go-to' hotel when visiting the city!

I stayed at Mademoiselle in late July with my wife. Our room was small, but we chose not to spend extra for a larger room. Still, it was tight. But however small it was, it was very nicely appointed and clean. The staff was very nice and friendly. I loved the breakfast buffet. There's a steam room downstairs, which was nice, but what really made this place stand out is the amazing indoor pool with a waterfall shower in it. That was bliss.

A very clean and new hotel with outstanding staff. Rooms are average size for Paris, so no surprise. The shower is new and works very well. We are not breakfast people, so we had espresso brought to the room each morning. As others have written, the pool is brand-spanking new and very clean. The steam bath is often not hot enough, something which could be easily remedied. The hotel is on a quiet street within easy walking access to the Commerce metro. If I was to give one recommendation, I would suggest that you purchase pates, roast chicken, foie gras and several salads from the Boucherie du Square on Rue du Commerce. There is also a cheesemonger on the same street. We purchased all that plus bread and wine (also on the same street) and had a wonderful picnic on the 4th-floor terrace of the hotel. The staff provided us plates, wine glasses and utensils and even cleared everything away. Frankly, this was one of our best meals in Paris. There are also neighborhood bistros for coffee or beer/wine. This locale is great if you want to get away from the hustle bustle of the more touristy areas yet still be within easy reach via subway.

The room (204) was very small and the view was not as good as we were expecting other than that the hotel was good and the staff were very friendly. Our room was facing the front side right accross from an store were they sale guns and knifes.

A very good hotel, located 300 m from the metro and within walking distance from the Eiffel tower in a very welcoming neighborhood. Rooms are clean and spacious compared to other rooms we saw in Paris. Staff were great

A good modern hotel with a great location, very friendly staff, can’t do enough for you, set in a typical cafe culture area of Paris, with many local independent shops with 5 mins walk from ‘Comerce’ Metro.

we spent lovely moments at Les Jardins de Mademoiselle "elegant newly boutique hotel at le 15eme". the location is perfect "shops, coffee houses, metro near by, ect.."
We had 2 connected rooms "family" spacious and nicely decorated, the beds are so comfortable, you can also grab your mug and sit the lovely green terrace at the 4th floor.
Finally i would extremely thank the amazing staff at the front desk "very hospitable and helpful".
Thank you all and surely i will recommend your hotel.

Pros.: Everything is new. Clean and modern. Pool is beutifull. Terace is also very nice. Employees are very nice. Rooms are big, each room had 2 T.V.'s. And the design is beutifull. Wifi is free of charge.

Cons: Bath is not comftable. Difficult to step out from bath without sliping. Also the tap is not suitable to the sink. So it's not easy to wash face. Vew from the room is nice but not as nice as promised. Breakfest isn't included.

Came here on opening day. Fab hotel, brand new and clean. Excellent location and excellent staff. Highly recommend this hotel when staying in Paris. I stayed here for business and my room was quiet which is essential for me.
